Package: asar-snes
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: SNES 65816/SPC700/SuperFX cross-assembler
 asar is a multi-architecture cross-assembler targeting the SNES and its
 co-processors: 65816 (main CPU), SPC700 (audio DSP), and SuperFX (graphics
 co-processor). Used extensively for SNES ROM hacking, homebrew development,
 and Super Mario World ROM hacking toolchains.
 .
 Features include a macro system, math expressions, RAM map tables,
 multiple pass assembly, symbol file output (wla/nocash format), and
 optional ROM checksum fixing. Reads an .asm source file and patches or
 creates a .sfc/.smc ROM.
 .
 Installed as asar-snes to coexist with the @electron/asar npm tool.
